Implemented the repository `extends` mechanism so a downstream `cookieplone-config.json` can declare an upstream and inherit, override, add, or hide its templates with downstream-wins merge semantics. Template entries merge per-field, so partial redeclares like `{"hidden": true}` inherit `path` / `title` / `description` from upstream; when a downstream supplies its own `path`, the downstream template directory is overlaid on top of the upstream tree at render time so individual files (e.g. `README.md`) can be overridden without copying the upstream wholesale. Supports tag pinning, transitive chains, cycle detection, and a depth limit. @ericof
